<item>
            <title>[PDFBOX-5261] Signing a full scanned PDF causes &quot;The signature byte range is invalid&quot;</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-5261</link>
                <project id="12310760" key="PDFBOX">PDFBox</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Signing with:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;pdfbox-app-3.0.0-20210804.050614-2786.jar causes the invalid signature.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;pdfbox-app-2.0.24.jar causes a valid signature.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;By full scanned document I mean that the document is full of images.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The attachment &quot;unsigned.pdf&quot; is the first file that I couldn&apos;t sign.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The attachment &quot;file.pdf&quot; is the second file that I couldn&apos;t sign also.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The attachment &quot;file_signed.pdf&quot; is the result of signing &quot;file.pdf&quot;. With Adobe Reader you can check that the signature is invalid.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Maybe it is related to having tables and images in the document.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
