                            <comment id="17401258" author="mkl" created="Wed, 18 Aug 2021 17:09:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Both&#160;&lt;span class=&quot;nobr&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/attachment/13032139/13032139_file.pdf&quot; title=&quot;file.pdf attached to PDFBOX-5261&quot;&gt;file.pdf&lt;sup&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;rendericon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/link_attachment_7.gif&quot; height=&quot;7&quot; width=&quot;7&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#160;and&#160;unsigned.pdf (in &lt;span class=&quot;nobr&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/attachment/13032136/13032136_unsigned.part1.rar&quot; title=&quot;unsigned.part1.rar attached to PDFBOX-5261&quot;&gt;unsigned.part1.rar&lt;sup&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;rendericon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/link_attachment_7.gif&quot; height=&quot;7&quot; width=&quot;7&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;...) have hybrid cross references. In&#160;&lt;span class=&quot;nobr&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/attachment/13032140/13032140_file_signed.pdf&quot; title=&quot;file_signed.pdf attached to PDFBOX-5261&quot;&gt;file_signed.pdf&lt;sup&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;rendericon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/link_attachment_7.gif&quot; height=&quot;7&quot; width=&quot;7&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;, though, we see that the incremental update created for the signature has a pure cross reference stream. That is invalid:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;If a file has been started with a pure cross reference table or hybrid references, all incremental updates must also use&#160;pure cross reference tables or hybrid references.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;If a file has been started with a pure cross reference stream, all incremental updates must also use&#160;pure cross reference streams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17683246" author="jira-bot" created="Thu, 2 Feb 2023 07:06:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 1907217 from lehmi@apache.org in branch &apos;pdfbox/trunk&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/r1907217&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/r1907217&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-5261&quot; title=&quot;Signing a full scanned PDF causes &amp;quot;The signature byte range is invalid&amp;quot;&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-5261&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-5261&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: force pure xref tables when doing incremental updates on hybrid pdfs&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17683249" author="lehmi" created="Thu, 2 Feb 2023 07:17:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve fixed the writer. Pure cross reference tables are forced for Incremental updates of hybrid pdfs.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The detection of hybrid pdfs is suboptimal and I&apos;m working on an improvement&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17684153" author="jira-bot" created="Sat, 4 Feb 2023 12:03:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 1907263 from lehmi@apache.org in branch &apos;pdfbox/trunk&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/r1907263&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/r1907263&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-5261&quot; title=&quot;Signing a full scanned PDF causes &amp;quot;The signature byte range is invalid&amp;quot;&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-5261&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-5261&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: fix detecttion of hybrid cross references and simplify&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17684154" author="lehmi" created="Sat, 4 Feb 2023 12:09:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve finally fixed the detection of hybrid cross references. PDFBox now should handle incremental updates of pdfs using hybrid cross references correctly.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
